16:19.800 --> 16:21.680
a lot of stuff, either of VS Code itself

16:21.680 --> 16:22.840
or the whole computer.

16:23.840 --> 16:24.680
I don't know.

16:25.040 --> 16:27.200
Definitely one of the ones that annoys me the most,

16:27.200 --> 16:28.880
and sometimes I just end up disabling it

16:28.880 --> 16:30.120
because it's so annoying.

16:30.120 --> 16:34.920
The purpose of the npm script you wrote

16:34.920 --> 16:39.160
is only if somebody doesn't have prettier installed

16:39.160 --> 16:40.440
in their editor, correct?

16:41.600 --> 16:45.520
It's amongst the reasons that I would do it.

16:45.520 --> 16:47.240
Probably the chief reason is so that I can now

16:47.240 --> 16:48.800
run it in CI, CD, right?

16:48.800 --> 16:50.920
So, I can run it as like a GitHub action,

16:50.920 --> 16:53.640
so then it won't check in my, or it won't deploy my code

16:53.640 --> 16:56.000
if it's like failing lint or failing prettier.

16:56.920 --> 16:58.880
That's probably the biggest reason

16:58.880 --> 17:01.040
because almost everyone that I work with

17:01.040 --> 17:04.880
or have worked with has some version of prettier

17:04.880 --> 17:06.480
or lint built into their editor

17:06.480 --> 17:08.320
and they just fix it on the fly,

17:08.320 --> 17:10.160
and there's a few holdouts that'll just run it

17:10.160 --> 17:12.720
right before they commit, right?

17:12.720 --> 17:15.600
So, those are the two chief reasons I do it.

